DOC.TE:
   Originally a health mint ("For that stormy breath!"), peppermint
LifeSavers entered millions of pockets and purses. Over the years 24
more flavors were added (Wild Cherry, 1934; Five Flavors, 1935;
Butterscotch, 1951). Others were abandoned (Anise, 1934;
Molas-O-Mint, 1942, and Root Beer, 1968).

   For other information, Consulate General of Peru, Tourist
Information, 3450 Wilshire Blvd., Suite 800, Los Angeles, CA 90010;
(213) 252-5910, fax (213) 252-8130.

   Grace Bay Club; Providenciales; (800) 946-1999;
www.gracebayclub.com; Swank Spanish-style villa resort on Grace Bay.
Rates, including breakfast, from $675 per couple, per night.

   Education: Bachelor's degree in business administration from USC;
master's in business administration from Harvard; certified public
accountant.

